contentrichtext.text: '''GZ''' or '''gz''' may refer to: * [[Gaza Strip]] (FIPS PUB 10-4 territory code) * DIN 19303 Code for ''Gestrichener Zellstoffkarton'' (German), a grade of paperboard also known as [[solid bleached board]] * [[Godzone]] - a phrase used by New Zealanders to describe their homeland * [[Ground Zero]], in military parlance * [[Guangzhou]] * [[Guizhou]], China * [[Air Rarotonga]] IATA airline designator * Righting torque, righting arm or GZ acting to restore a tilting ship to the vertical â€” see [[metacentric height]] * A [[Leet|leetspeak]] word meaning "congratulations" (from leetspeak "gratz") * [[Metal Gear Solid: Ground Zeroes]], an upcoming video game * .gz, the file extension for [[gzip]] files (GNU zip, an open source file compression program) {{disambig}}
